 gap in knowledge, allowing work to begin comparing specific laws of the Qumran sect with rabbinic laws. With the publication of scroll 4QMMT-a polemical letter by Dead Sea sectarians concerning points of Jewish law-an effective comparison was finally possible. This is the first book-length treatment of the material to appear since the publication of 4QMMT and the first attempt to apply its discoveries to the work of nineteenth-century scholars. It is also the first work on this important topic written in plain language and accessible to nonspecialists in the history of Jewish law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJewish lawxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aJudaismxHistoryyTo 70 A.D. 0aQumran community. 0aRabbinical literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  a19th century.  a4qmmt.  acomprehensive study.  aconservative religion.  acultural studies.  adead sea scrolls.  ahalakhah.  ajewish history.  ajewish law.  ajewish practice.  ajewish scholars.  ajewish studies.  ajudaism.  alegal literature.  alegal material.  anonfiction.  apharisaic.  apolemical letter.  aqumran.  arabbinic judaism.  arabbinic law.  arabbis.  areligious history.  areligious law.  areligious scholars.  areligious scholarship.  asadducees.  asecond temple.  asectarians.1 aShemesh, Aharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025910240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094503640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945036/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a